29/11/2004
BERLIN, Germany -- European Commission President Jose Manuel Barroso has said he believes the future decision on Turkey's EU membership bid should be formulated clearly. 
In an interview with Sunday's (28 November) German Bild am Sonntag, Barosso stressed that the EU member countries expect a detailed and open debate about the issue. 
He also repeated that Turkey's entry into the EU depended solely on the implementation of the set political and economic reforms. 
Ankara wants members to set a concrete date for the start of accession talks next month. 
(NTV - 28/11/04)
